rn Ireland)]]'''\n** [[Glentoran F.C.]] - 1969\u201370\n* '''[[Anglo-Italian Cup]]'''\n** [[Newcastle United F.C.]] - [[1973 Anglo-Italian Cup]]\n* '''[[Texaco Cup]]: 2'''\n** [[Newcastle United F.C.]] - 1973\u201374, 1974\u201375\n* '''[[Football League Third Division]]'''\n** [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] - [[1981\u201382 Football League|1981\u201382]]\n* '''[[Cypriot Cup]]'''\n** [[APOEL F.C.|APOEL]] - 1983\u201384\n* '''[[LTV Super Cup]]'''\n** [[APOEL F.C.|APOEL]] - 1984\n\n===As a manager===\n* '''[[Cypriot First Division]]'''\n** [[APOEL F.C.|APOEL]] - [[1985\u201386 Cypriot First Division|1985\u201386]]\n* '''[[LTV Super Cup]]'''\n** [[APOEL F.C.|APOEL]] - 1986\n* '''[[Irish Cup]]'''\n** [[Glentoran F.C.]] 1995\u201396\n* '''[[Gold Cup (Northern Ireland)]]'''\n** [[Glentoran F.C.]] 1994\u201395\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\nhttps://web.archive.org/web/20110413080831/http://www.whitby-town.com/news10.php\n\nNewly appointed manager of Blyth Spartans\nhttps://web.archive.org/web/20120611044429/http://blythspartansafc.co.uk/new_php/?p=7718\n\n==External links==\n*[http://nifootball.blogspot.com/2006/08/tommy-cassidy.html Northern Ireland's Footballing Greats: Tommy Cassidy]\n\n{{Northern Ireland Squad 1982 World Cup}}\n\n{{APOEL FC managers}}\n{{Gateshead F.C. managers}}\n{{Glentoran F.C. managers}}\n{{Sligo Rovers F.C. managers}}\n{{Workington A.F.C. managers}}\n{{Whitby Town F.C. managers}}\n{{Blyth Spartans F.C. managers |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cassidy, Tommy}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Belfast]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association footballers from Northern Ireland]]\n[[Category:Northern Ireland international footballers]]\n[[Category:1982 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Glentoran F.C. players]]\n[[Category:NIFL Premiership players]]\n[[Category:Newcastle United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Burnley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Cypriot First Division players]